# gitleaks fingerprint allowlist
#
# One fingerprint per line. Format:
#   <commit-sha>:<file>:<rule>:<line>
#
# Each entry needs a comment explaining *why* the match is benign — if
# you cannot articulate that in one line, the value is probably a real
# secret and should be rotated, not allowlisted.
#
# Inline ``# gitleaks:allow`` comments only suppress matches in commits
# that contain the comment. Historical commits the scanner walks (via
# ``--log-opts`` or default scan mode) still trip the rule unless the
# fingerprint is listed here.

# tests/test_pricing_limits_visible.py — Stripe test placeholder, never
# a real key. The string ``sk_test_placeholder`` matches the
# ``stripe-access-token`` rule (``(sk|pk|rk)_(test|live)_[0-9a-z]{10,99}``)
# because "placeholder" is 11 chars. The test sets
# ``settings.stripe_secret_key`` to a non-empty truthy value to exercise
# the live-pricing branch of the page builder; nothing more.
